						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">qwertymodo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">the decoding actually only cares that A14 is low (rather than A15:13 = 101).<br /></div>Per what <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=181040#p181040" class="postlink">Gekkio said</a>, /CS is asserted for the memory range from $A000-$FDFF. On the DMG, it's specifically asserted after the first half master cycle, for the remaining 3.5 master cycles.<br /><br />Other that timing difference, at least on DMG, there's no functional difference between (/CS=0 AND A14=0) and (A[15..13]='b'101).<br /><br />Obviously Gekkio's data only concerns the DMG; the GBC and GBA's timing and ranges need to be compared.<br /><br />... also, those linked timing graphs are subtly different from their graphs in their <a href="https://github.com/Gekkio/gb-ctr" class="postlink">Complete Technical Reference</a>.</div>

